commitMessage:

Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 8e2f55de9148065559a27268ce07d79009b9892a by Brad Bishop

This changes don't require any other outstanding commits right?  The only coreq to this merging would be the adding of the service files into phosphor-logging?

Otherwise, It would be good to put these in a separate commit so we don't hold up phosphor-logging changes.
We will need phosphor-logging group a bit later. This PR depends on phosphor-logging repo's change that will ship service files and busconfig ACL.

Question: I noticed that this takes the name of the service when you moved this to the repo. I was trying to find documentation on where this gets set but could not. Do you have any pointers for how you figured this out?

It's substituted by bitbake/phosphor class that installs the service file.
In the individual repo the BUSNAME has been replaced with actual value.
The "nobranch=1" can be removed now that the phosphor-logging commit has been merged.

I believe we're still waiting on the SRCREV bump right? https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/43057

We will also want to remove the SRCREV bump below after the bump is done.
Correct. Waiting for a srcrev bump.
